---
const pageTitle = "Plancha360 | Outdoor cooking, made social";
const pageDescription =
	"Plancha360 is a premium-accessible outdoor cooking brand built around shared meals, warm gatherings, and the urge to cook together.";
import ProductViewer3D from "../components/ProductViewer3D.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>{pageTitle}</title>
		<meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
		<meta name="theme-color" content="#f3ebdf" />
		<script type="module" src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/model-viewer/3.4.0/model-viewer.min.js"></script>
		</head>
	<body>
		<main class="site-shell">
			<header class="topbar">
				<a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Plancha360 home">
					<img src="/images/logo/plancha360-logo.svg" alt="Plancha360" />
					<span>Plancha360</span>
				</a>
				<nav aria-label="Primary">
					<a href="#product">Product</a>
					<a href="#story">Brand story</a>
					<a href="#waitlist">Waitlist</a>
				</nav>
			</header>

			<section class="hero" id="top">
				<div class="hero-copy">
					<div class="eyebrow">Outdoor cooking, made social</div>
					<h1>Cook together. Stay longer. Make the evening the point.</h1>
					<p class="lede">
						Plancha360 is a premium-accessible outdoor cooking brand built for warm gatherings, relaxed hosting, and the kind of
						moments people remember because they happened around the fire.
					</p>

					<div class="hero-actions">
						<a class="button button-primary" href="#waitlist">Join the waitlist</a>
						<a class="button button-secondary" href="#product">See the product</a>
					</div>

					<div class="trust-row" aria-label="Key brand promises">
						<span>Social first</span>
						<span>Warm, bold, modern</span>
						<span>Built to last</span>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="hero-visual">
					<ProductViewer3D />
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="intro-grid" aria-label="Brand summary" id="story">
				<article>
					<p class="eyebrow">Show, don’t tell</p>
					<h2>The feeling comes first.</h2>
					<p>
						The site should make people feel the scene before they read the specs: warm fire, easy hosting, shared plates,
						and a product that brings everyone closer without feeling precious or intimidating.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article>
					<p class="eyebrow">Built for the first customer</p>
					<h2>Home hosts first. Then events. Then hospitality.</h2>
					<p>
						The immediate job is to convince people who love hosting that this is the grill they want at the center of the
						evening. Everything else comes later.
					</p>
				</article>
			</section>

			<section id="product" class="section">
				<div class="section-heading">
					<p class="eyebrow">The product</p>
					<h2>One object. Multiple reasons to gather.</h2>
					<p>
						Plancha360 should feel clear in seconds: a steel outdoor cooking object that is premium enough to trust, accessible
						enough to want, and social enough to become the center of the night.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="card-grid models">
					<article class="card model-card">
						<img src="/images/products/model-900.png" alt="Plancha360 Model 900" />
						<div>
							<h3>Model 900</h3>
							<p>900 mm diameter · 5 mm grill plate · hip-high format for shared outdoor cooking and bigger gatherings.</p>
						</div>
					</article>
					<article class="card model-card">
						<img src="/images/products/model-700.png" alt="Plancha360 Model 700" />
						<div>
							<h3>Model 700</h3>
							<p>700 mm diameter · 5 mm grill plate · the smaller version for tighter patios and easier setups.</p>
						</div>
					</article>
					<article class="card model-card">
						<img src="/images/products/product-01.png" alt="Plancha360 product detail" />
						<div>
							<h3>Why it matters</h3>
							<p>It is not just hardware. It is the anchor of the evening: cook, talk, serve, stay.</p>
						</div>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section split">
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">What it solves</p>
					<h2>People buy the feeling, then the function.</h2>
					<p>
						The brand should answer the real objections without sounding defensive: why it is worth the money, where it fits,
						how practical it is, and why it is safe and durable enough to become part of real life.
					</p>
				</div>
				<ul class="benefits">
					<li>Turns cooking into a social event instead of a solo task.</li>
					<li>Feels premium, but not cold or exclusive.</li>
					<li>Simple enough to understand in seconds.</li>
					<li>Credible enough to justify the price.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="section showcase">
				<div class="section-heading">
					<p class="eyebrow">Social proof</p>
					<h2>Make it obvious that this belongs at the center of a good gathering.</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="showcase-grid">
					<div class="visual-card">
						<img src="/images/lifestyle/lifestyle-01.png" alt="A large outdoor gathering around Plancha360" />
					</div>
					<div class="showcase-copy">
						<h3>Warm, human, modern.</h3>
						<p>
							The best shots are the ones that show the product in use: people moving around it, sharing food, talking,
							and keeping the moment going.
						</p>
						<p>
							That is the emotion we want: not “look at this object,” but “I want that evening.”
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section roadmap">
				<div class="roadmap-card">
					<p class="eyebrow">Roadmap</p>
					<h2>Launch first, then expand.</h2>
					<p>
						Waitlist now. Direct purchase next. Rentals later. Once the prototype arrives, the site can grow with real use-case
						content: party cooking, casual grilling, how-to videos, care guides, and event imagery.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section" id="waitlist">
				<div class="section-heading">
					<p class="eyebrow">Waitlist</p>
					<h2>Be first when Plancha360 opens.</h2>
					<p>
						For now, the main goal is interest collection. This form is the starting point for launch demand and future orders.
					</p>
				</div>

				<form class="waitlist-form">
					<label>
						Name
						<input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" />
					</label>
					<label>
						Email
						<input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" />
					</label>
					<label>
						What are you planning?
						<select name="intent">
							<option>Hosting at home</option>
							<option>Buying as a gift</option>
							<option>Event / rental interest</option>
							<option>Just curious</option>
						</select>
					</label>
					<label class="full-width">
						Message
						<textarea name="message" rows="5" placeholder="Tell us what you want to cook, host, or build around Plancha360."></textarea>
					</label>
					<button class="button button-primary full-width" type="submit">Join the waitlist</button>
				</form>
			</section>

			<section class="section faq">
				<div class="section-heading">
					<p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
					<h2>Clear answers, no supplier noise.</h2>
				</div>

				<details open>
					<summary>Who is this for?</summary>
					<p>People who host, love outdoor cooking, and want something that feels premium without becoming a luxury flex object.</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Can I order directly?</summary>
					<p>That is the next phase. The site should support direct checkout later, but the immediate launch goal is waitlist interest.</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Will rentals be available?</summary>
					<p>Yes, later the site can expand to event rentals once the core brand and product flow are established.</p>
				</details>
			</section>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:global(:root) {
		color-scheme: light;
		--bg: #f3eadf;
		--panel: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
		--panel-strong: #fffaf4;
		--text: #1d1815;
		--muted: #665952;
		--border: rgba(29, 24, 21, 0.12);
		--accent: #b6532a;
		--accent-2: #2f4b45;
		--shadow: 0 26px 90px rgba(63, 40, 20, 0.14);
		font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
	}

	:global(html) {
		background:
			radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(182, 83, 42, 0.16), transparent 40%),
			radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(47, 75, 69, 0.12), transparent 32%),
			var(--bg);
			color: var(--text);
	}

	:global(body) {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 100vh;
	}

	:global(img) {
		display: block;
		max-width: 100%;
	}

	.site-shell {
		max-width: 1180px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 24px 20px 72px;
	}

	.topbar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 20px;
		padding: 14px 6px 22px;
	}

	.brand {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		text-decoration: none;
		color: var(--text);
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	.brand img {
		width: 36px;
		height: 36px;
		object-fit: contain;
	}

	nav {
		display: flex;
		gap: 18px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	nav a {
		text-decoration: none;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.hero,
	.section,
	.intro-grid article,
	.roadmap-card {
		background: var(--panel);
		backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 30px;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow);
	}

	.hero {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(0, 0.95fr);
		gap: 28px;
		padding: 44px;
	}

	.hero-copy {
		align-self: center;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 12px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		font-size: 0.76rem;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3,
	p {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 6.4vw, 6.2rem);
		line-height: 0.93;
		max-width: 11ch;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		text-wrap: balance;
	}

	.lede {
		font-size: 1.12rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		max-width: 60ch;
		color: var(--muted);
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	.hero-actions {
		display: flex;
		gap: 14px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 14px 20px;
		min-height: 48px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 700;
		border: 1px solid transparent;
	}

	.button-primary {
		background: var(--text);
		color: white;
	}

	.button-secondary {
		border-color: rgba(29, 24, 21, 0.16);
		color: var(--text);
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.42);
	}

	.trust-row {
		display: flex;
		gap: 12px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.trust-row span {
		padding: 10px 14px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.92rem;
	}

	.hero-visual {
		display: grid;
		gap: 16px;
		align-content: start;
	}

	.visual-card {
		overflow: hidden;
		border-radius: 24px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(29, 24, 21, 0.1);
		background: #e8ddd0;
		box-shadow: 0 18px 40px rgba(45, 30, 18, 0.12);
	}

	.visual-card img {
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		object-fit: cover;
	}

	.visual-card-large {
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
	}

	.visual-stack {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
		gap: 16px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	.visual-card-small {
		aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
	}

	.hero-note {
		display: grid;
		align-content: end;
		padding: 22px;
		border-radius: 24px;
		background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(182, 83, 42, 0.12), rgba(47, 75, 69, 0.08));
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.hero-note p:last-child {
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.intro-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 18px;
		margin: 18px 0;
	}

	.intro-grid article,
	.section,
	.roadmap-card {
		padding: 28px;
	}

	.section {
		margin-top: 18px;
	}

	.section-heading {
		max-width: 62ch;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.card-grid,
	.benefits {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 16px;
	}

	.card,
	.benefits li,
	details {
		padding: 22px;
		border-radius: 20px;
		background: var(--panel-strong);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.model-card {
		display: grid;
		gap: 16px;
	}

	.model-card img {
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
		object-fit: cover;
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(29, 24, 21, 0.08);
	}

	.card p,
	.intro-grid p,
	.section p,
	details p,
	li {
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.split {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 24px;
		align-items: start;
	}

	.benefits {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
	}

	.showcase-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(0, 0.8fr);
		gap: 20px;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.showcase-copy {
		padding: 4px 6px;
	}

	.roadmap-card {
		background: linear-gradient(140deg, rgba(182, 83, 42, 0.12), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5));
	}

	.waitlist-form {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 16px;
	}

	label {
		display: grid;
		gap: 8px;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	input,
	select,
	textarea {
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.84);
		font: inherit;
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.full-width {
		grid-column: 1 / -1;
	}

	.faq {
		display: grid;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	details summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	@media (max-width: 980px) {
		.hero,
		.showcase-grid,
		.split {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.card-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.visual-stack {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 780px) {
		.topbar {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}

		.intro-grid,
		.waitlist-form {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		h1 {
			max-width: none;
		}

		.hero {
			padding: 28px 20px;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.site-shell {
			padding-inline: 14px;
		}

		.section,
		.intro-grid article,
		.hero,
		.roadmap-card {
			border-radius: 22px;
		}

		.button {
			width: 100%;
		}
	}
</style>
